Determine the output of the following code:

```java
// System.out.println("Line 1");
System.out.println("Line 2");
/* System.out.println("Line 3"); */
System.out.println("Line 4");
```

What is printed when the following code runs?

```java
int score = 100;
// score = 0;
System.out.println(score);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 5;
// x = 10;
x += 3;
/* x = 20; */
System.out.println(x);
```

Consider the following method:

```java
/**
 * Precondition: divisor != 0
 */
public static int divide(int dividend, int divisor) {
    return dividend / divisor;
}
```

Which of the following best describes the purpose of the precondition comment?

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
int x = 4;
int y = 1;
// x = x + 10;
x = x + y;
/*
y = y + 5;
x = x * 2;
*/
System.out.print(x + " " + y);
```

Consider the following method comment.

```java
/**
 * Precondition: score >= 0
 * Postcondition: returns true if score is at least 60;
 * otherwise returns false
 */
public static boolean passing(int score)
{
    return score >= 60;
}
```

Which of the following best describes the comment?
